Exactly four months after berating a fan for begging him for help on social media, singer Olamide has gifted him a car gift, howbeit secretly The fan identified as Odunuga Oluwaseun had jokingly asked for a car gift from Olamide. The singer responded he owed the young man no gift, carpeting him to the astonishment of netizens.   Tuface, others visit late Sound Sultan’s grave     Chimamanda Adichie recalls last moments with mom     Seven Nigerian musicians who rose to fame from slums   Olamide had said: “Money wey you keep for my hand. Ori iya e gba le.” The fan however in a thankful post, revealed the singer pulled through with his plan and gifted him a car. Although Olamide had not reacted to the claim, the fan wrote: “Today, I’m so happy because I be car owner by this post. @Olamide went out of all odds to put a smile on my face. You are so special. plus na low key you do am. I go post am. I love you more. Thank you boss.@asakemuski manager. you no go fall.”